==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filaria
<hw>Fi*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>filariae</plw>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>filum</ets> a
thread.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>a small, slender nematode worm of
the family <fam>Onchocercidae</fam> (<fam>Filariidae</fam>) of many
species, parasitic when adult in various animals, including man. They
may live within the blood, or in other bodily fluids, or within tissues
or cavities of the body. Infection with such organisms may be
transmitted by blood-sucking arthropods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filaria</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Filaria
<hw>Fi*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>filum</ets> a thread.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>a former genus
comprised of certain nematodes, now classed as belonging to several
genera within the family <fam>Onchocercidae</fam>. See
<er>Onchocerca</er> and <er>Guinea worm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filarial</ent>⟦br⟧
